<div id="v230.131.2"><span class="H7737 s">Surely I have behaved</span><span class="H1826 s"> and quieted</span><span class="H5315 s"> myself</span><span class="H1580 s">, as a child that is weaned</span><span class="H517 s"> of his mother</span><span class="H5315 s">: my soul</span><span class="H1580 s"> <i>is</i> even as a weaned child</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (myself: Heb. my soul)</span></div> 
<div id="v230.131.3"><span class="H3478 s">Let Israel</span><span class="H3176 s"> hope</span><span class="H3068 s"> in the LORD</span><span class="H5704 s"> from henceforth and for</span><span class="H5769 s"> ever</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (henceforth: Heb. now)</span></div></div> 
